    </a>
    
  </div>
</div>

    
  
    
      







  







  


<div class="media stream-item">
  <div class="media-body">

    <div class="section-subheading article-title mb-0 mt-0">
      <a href="/publication/replication-journals/" >No Room at the Inn? The Case for Dedicated Replication Journals</a>
    </div>

    
    <a href="/publication/replication-journals/"  class="summary-link">
      <div class="article-style">
        This article reviews the scarcity of published replications in economics and psychology, examines why traditional journals resist publishing them, and argues that dedicated replication journals offer an essential solution by providing critical infrastructure for the self-correcting function of science.
      </div>
    </a>
    

    <div class="stream-meta article-metadata">

      

      
      <div>
        

  <span >
      <a href="/author/w.-robert-reed/">W. Robert Reed</a></span>, <span >
      <a href="/author/lukas-roseler/">Lukas Röseler</a></span>, <span >
      <a href="/author/marianne-saam/">Marianne Saam</a></span>, <span >
      <a href="/author/dr-lukas-wallrich/">Dr Lukas Wallrich</a></span>
      </div>
      
    </div>

    
    <div class="btn-links">
      





  
  
    
  
<a class="btn btn-outline-primary btn-page-header btn-sm" href="https://hdl.handle.net/10419/319083" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
  Preprint
</a>




  
















  
  
    
  
<a class="btn btn-outline-primary btn-page-header btn-sm" href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.socec.2025.102502" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
  Source Document
</a>


<a class="btn btn-outline-primary btn-page-header btn-sm" href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.socec.2025.102502" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
  DOI
</a>



    </div>
    

  </div>
